From e4e468f9337af0418e4b865aaa813714f67da155 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: vllm-shim <vllm-shim@local>
Date: Thu, 1 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] fix(communicator): disable MLP allreduce fusion under DP
 attention

should_fuse_mlp_allreduce_with_next_layer carries its own inline copy
of the aiter-allreduce-fusion condition, and that copy is missing the
`not is_dp_attention_enabled()` guard that both apply_aiter_all_reduce_fusion
and apply_flashinfer_allreduce_fusion have. With --enable-aiter-allreduce-fusion
and --enable-dp-attention set together, the function returns True, so
the MoE layer tags its output `_sglang_needs_allreduce_fusion` and skips
postprocess_layer (the FULL -> TP_ATTN_FULL reduce-scatter). The next
layer's prepare_attn then asks apply_aiter_all_reduce_fusion whether it
can take the fused path, gets False (DP attention), and falls back to a
plain all-reduce, which sums but does not reshape. Attention then runs
on the FULL-sized (num_tokens * dp_size) buffer instead of the per-rank
buffer; the MLA absorb path's KV-cache write hits a shape mismatch
against the per-rank out_cache_loc and crashes during CUDA graph
capture.

Generalize the pre-existing EAGLE-only DP guard in this function to all
DP attention: under DP attention the fusion shortcut is never valid
because FULL and TP_ATTN_FULL differ in token count. The EAGLE case was
a narrower instance of the same bug.

Found debugging Kimi K2.6 MXFP4 on 8x MI300X; not upstreamed.
---
 python/sglang/srt/layers/communicator.py | 17 ++++++++++++-----
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/python/sglang/srt/layers/communicator.py b/python/sglang/srt/layers/communicator.py
index 853cf3a..6ba33c6 100644
--- a/python/sglang/srt/layers/communicator.py
+++ b/python/sglang/srt/layers/communicator.py
@@ -720,11 +720,18 @@ class LayerCommunicator:
         if is_enable_moe_cp_allgather():
             return False
 
-        if (
-            is_dp_attention_enabled()
-            and self._speculative_algo is not None
-            and self._speculative_algo.is_eagle()
-        ):
+        # DP attention runs MoE in FULL mode but attention in
+        # TP_ATTN_FULL mode, and the two differ in token count. The
+        # fusion path defers the MoE all-reduce into the next layer's
+        # prepare_attn and skips postprocess_layer's FULL -> TP_ATTN_FULL
+        # reduce-scatter; the deferred all-reduce sums but does not
+        # reshape, so attention then runs on the FULL-sized buffer and
+        # the KV-cache write shape-mismatches the per-rank out_cache_loc.
+        # apply_aiter_all_reduce_fusion and apply_flashinfer_allreduce_fusion
+        # already exclude DP attention; the inline aiter check below does
+        # not, so guard the whole function here. Supersedes the narrower
+        # EAGLE-only guard that previously lived here.
+        if is_dp_attention_enabled():
             return False
 
         if get_attn_tp_context().input_scattered:
